articles.title: Yahoo Finance
articles.content: Stock markets mostly bumped upwards Thursday as hopes grew that the European Union could strike a trade deal with the United States, while Tesla shares nosedived on poor earnings results. Briefing.com analyst Patrick O'Hare said Trump's Tuesday trade announcement with Japan had raised hopes about further agreements. "There is underlying enthusiasm for more trade deals being struck before the August 1 deadline," O'Hare said. This was boosted further by "optimism surrounding trade talks between the US and EU", said Joshua Mahony, chief market analyst at Rostro trading group. articles.title: Motorcycle skids, gets dragged by taxi on PIE
articles.content: The rider was taken to hospital while the taxi driver is assisting with investigations. The police told Stomp they were alerted to the incident at about 5.30pm. The rider was taken conscious to the hospital, a police spokesperson said. A 69-year-old taxi driver is assisting with investigations. A video posted on ROADS.sg's Facebook page shows the motorcycle skidding and falling onto the road. The taxi did not stop throughout the incident. Netizens speculated that the rider may have hit a pothole before losing control of his bike. Many also questioned why the taxi driver failed to stop after the collision. Stomp has contacted Strides Premier for comment.
